{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T09:06:48.063Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What Step/Exponential Decay Are"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step Decay"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Exponential Decay"},{"type":"text","text":" are two popular learning rate scheduling strategies that reduce the learning rate over time as training progresses."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The core idea: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Start with a high learning rate"},{"type":"text","text":" for fast initial learning, then "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"gradually reduce it"},{"type":"text","text":" as the model gets closer to the optimal solution, enabling finer adjustments."}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Strategy"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"How It Works"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Step Decay"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Reduces learning rate by a fixed factor after a fixed number of epochs/steps"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Exponential Decay"}]}